<TITLE> Dhaka condemns Mumbai attacks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  Bangladesh on Thursday condemned the terrorist attack on India's financial capital of Mumbai. Foreign adviser Iftekhar Ahmed Chowdhury termed the bombing as `cowardly act' and expressed solidarity with New Delhi. "I condemn it as a mindless act of terror." "I wish to underscore that terror can serve no purpose. Our hearts are with those who have been affected by this cowardly bombing ." The foreign adviser also sent a letter to Indian external affairs minister Pranab Mukherjee bd
